```markdown In C#, you define an abstract class using the abstract keyword. An abstract class can contain abstract methods, which are method signatures without an implementation. Abstract methods must also use the abstract keyword and do not have a body. Any class inheriting from the abstract class must provide an implementation for all abstract methods.

